Yes and no.  You will see the boolean keywords (they aren't actually constants) is the case making sure actually is a boolean, not a string/int.<p><pre><code>    $x = "";
    if ( $x == false ) {} #yes
    if ( $x === false ) {} #no
</code></pre>
Edit: this is very useful for allowing a string search/manipulation function to return an error condition.<p><pre><code>    $str = string_function(...)
    if ( $str === false ) {
        #error
    } else {
        #continue processing $str
    }</code></pre>
